      "references": "[EFRS93] Erd\\H{o}s, Paul and Faudree, R. J. and Rousseau, C. C. and Schelp, R. H., Ramsey size linear graphs. Combin. Probab. Comput. (1993), 389-399.",
      "remarks": "In other words, is $G$ Ramsey size linear? This fails for a graph $G$ with $n$ vertices and $2n-2$ edges (for example with $H=K_n$). Erd\\H{o}s, Faudree, Rousseau, and Schelp \\cite{EFRS93} have shown that any graph $G$ with $n$ vertices and at most $n+1$ edges is Ramsey size linear.\n\nImplies [567].\n\nThis problem is #31 in Ramsey Theory in the graphs problem collection."
    },
